  "prompt": "My mom makes me eat less than my BMR for weight loss. what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're experiencing this. Your health and well-being are incredibly important. Eating less than your Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) can be harmful, as your body needs a minimum amount of energy to function properly. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Talk to a Healthcare Professional:** Reach out to a doctor, registered dietitian, or another healthcare provider. They can assess your nutritional needs and provide guidance tailored to your situation.\n\n2. **Communicate with Your Mom:** If you're comfortable, try having an open and honest conversation with your mom about how this is affecting you. Share your concerns and how it makes you feel.\n\n3. **Seek Support:** Consider speaking with a trusted adult, such as a teacher, school counselor, or another family member. They can offer support and help mediate the conversation with your mom if needed.\n\n4. **Educate Yourself and Your Family:** Understanding the importance of proper nutrition can help. Sometimes, sharing information about healthy eating habits and the risks of undereating can encourage positive changes.\n\n5. **Practice Self-Care:** Ensure you're taking care of your mental and emotional well-being. Engage in activities that make you feel good and reduce stress.\n\nRemember, your health is paramount, and you deserve support to ensure you're taking care of yourself in a healthy and balanced way.",
